description: From Middle English disacustome, from Old French desacostumer (“render unfamiliar”) (compare French désaccoutumer).

verbs.description: disaccustom (third-person singular simple present disaccustoms, present participle disaccustoming, simple past and past participle disaccustomed)

entries.meaning: to cause (someone) to break a habit or become unaccustomed to something that they are previously accustomed to
